{"profile":{"awsPrograms":[{"category":"Serverless","joinedAt":2026.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"COMMUNITY_BUILDER"},{"joinedAt":2026.0,"programName":"USER_GROUP_LEADER"},{"category":"Community Hero","joinedAt":2026.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"HERO"}],"basicInfo":{"alias":"margoneto81","avatar":"https://avatars.builderprofile.aws.dev/2zbapcZotzGkvmbop2GILVgwAdg.webp","bio":"I am a CTO/Solution Architect and the founder of the AWS User Group Basilicata. Based in Southern Italy, I have dedicated the last decade to building a thriving tech ecosystem in one of the most remote and beautiful regions of the country.\nMy passion lies in bridging the gap between high-level cloud innovation and local communities. I am the creator and organizer of 'Come To Code', an annual international conference held in the mountain village of Pignola. My mission is to prove that world-class technology can be shared and mastered anywhere, as long as there is a strong human connection behind it.\n\nKey Contributions & Expertise:\n\n- Community Leadership: 10+ years leading the Pignola Linux User Group (PLUG) and founding the AWS User Group Basilicata.\n- Event Architecture: Founder and lead organizer of 'Come To Code' (5+ editions), attracting speakers and attendees from across Europe to a small mountain village.\n- Public Speaking: Regular speaker at international and national conferences (NDC Copenhagen, Codemotion, DevFest, AWS Community Day Italy) focusing on Serverless, App Runner, and Python/Django.\n- Education & Mentorship: Promoting digital literacy through CoderDojo for kids, cybersecurity workshops in schools, and mentoring students in the 'Cloud Architecting on AWS' program at MT Academy.\n- Cloud Culture Advocate: Dedicated to showing how AWS services can empower local businesses and young talents in underserved regions.","builderProfileId":"b9a69c53-0622-4e59-a53a-38e230e7ef02","createdOn":1.738267426816E12,"headline":"Where code meets community: building bridges, not just architectures.","isStaff":false,"name":"Maurizio Argoneto"},"location":{"displayLocation":{"countryRegion":"IT"}},"profileStatus":"ACTIVE","socials":{"github":"https://github.com/argomauro/","linkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/argomauro/","personal":"https://sessionize.com/maurizio-argoneto/"}}}